countries.
The Wall Street Journal had
reported that

02:45.799 --> 02:52.105 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
U.S. officials agreed to talks,
without first
demanding the North give up its
nuclear program.

02:52.205 --> 02:57.511 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The White House says it insisted
the nuclear
issue be part of any talks, and
says that's

02:57.611 --> 03:03.216 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
consistent with longstanding
U.S. policy.
The North refused, and, days
later, carried

03:03.316 --> 03:05.185 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
out a nuclear test.

03:05.285 --> 03:10.257 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Days of violent
protests in Northern
India may finally be coming to
an end. The

03:10.357 --> 03:12.859 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
government agreed on concessions
late today.

03:12.959 --> 03:18.432 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
