killed at
least 19 people and cut off
water to New Delhi,

03:18.532 --> 03:21.902 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
as Jonathan Miller of
Independent Television
News reports.

03:22.002 --> 03:28.341 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JONATHAN MILLER: The angry
farmers of Haryana
have taken the bull by the
horns.

03:28.442 --> 03:32.913 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Feeling hard done by, thousands
have gone
on the rampage to protest
against a lack of

03:33.013 --> 03:39.753 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
prospects in a fragile new world
where many
fall through the cracks.
Paramilitary forces

03:39.853 --> 03:45.225 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
were ordered to shoot looters
and rioters
on sight, and they did.

03:45.325 --> 03:50.897 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Tonight, more than 10 million
people in Delhi
have no water to drink or to
wash in because

03:50.997 --> 03:56.536 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the protesters sabotaged the
Munak canal,
which provides the capital with
most of its

03:56.636 --> 04:04.945 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
water supply. The protesters
belong to the
Jat farming caste, of whom there
are 80 million

04:05.045 --> 04:12.853 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
across North India, eight
million in Haryana,
the state northwest of Delhi.

04:12.953 --> 04:19.359 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They want more government jobs
and places
in state education institutions,
half of which

04:19.459 --> 04:25.298 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are ring-fenced for what the
Indian government
calls other backward classes,
traditionally

04:25.398 --> 04:29.002 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
